                        <note>Possibly imperfect (cf. Bloomfield 3006, and suppl., a collection of quotations on virtues and vices). A catena of extracts from Bernard [of Clairvaux], Augustine, Gregory [the Great], ‘Longebardus’, Hugh of Saint-Victor, Ambrose, Jerome, Isidore of Seville, Seneca, Cassius, Bede, Anselm, John Chrysostom, Cyprian, Chrysogonus, with passages also from the Bible.</note>
