                        <handNote resp="#DM">Sporadically marginal annotations in hands from the Mainz Charterhouse, s. xv.</handNote>
                     </handDesc>
                     <decoDesc>
                        <decoNote resp="#DM" type="flourInit">A two-line red initial, with fleuronnée-like decoration in red and green. (fol. 17va)</decoNote>
                        <decoNote resp="#DM" type="colInit">Scribal red rubrics; hand A1) one- to three-line plain red initials, (fol. 2ra) flourished in the ink of the text; A2) at the beginning of a sentence majuscules in the ink of the text and highlighted in red, or larger capitals in red, green or blue, sometimes with decoration in red and green; paraphs, in red, green or blue.</decoNote>
                     </decoDesc>
                  </physDesc>
